Description

This lab contains a path traversal vulnerability in the product image functionality. The application validates that the filename ends with a specific extension (e.g., .png), but fails to handle null byte injection, allowing the extension check to be bypassed.

Objective

Retrieve the contents of the /etc/passwd file.

Steps to Solve
Intercept the request using Burp Suite while loading a product image.
Identify the parameter used to specify the image file (e.g., filename).

Modify the filename parameter to include a null byte injection:

../../../etc/passwd%00.png
Send the modified request to the server.
Observe that the response contains the contents of the /etc/passwd file.
Conclusion

The application relies on extension validation but does not properly handle null byte termination. This allows attackers to bypass the extension check and access sensitive files on the server.
